               <head>Arukh by Nathan ben Jehiel of Rome (vol. 2)</head>
               
               
               
               <msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85059886" rend="visible">
                  
                  
                  
                  <summary>A talmudic lexicon, volume 2.</summary>
                  
                  
                  
                  <textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="tmr-Hebr"/>
                  
                  
                  
                  <msItem rend="">
                     
                     
                     
                     <locus from="1r" to="153v"/>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="en">῾Arukh</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he">ערוך</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <author>
                        
                        
                        
                        <persName xml:lang="en" key="viaf.org/viaf/88359528">Nathan ben Jehiel, of Rome </persName>
                        
                        
                        
                        <persName xml:lang="he" key="viaf.org/viaf/88359528">נתן בן יחיאל, מרומה</persName>
                     
                     
                     
                     </author>
                     
                     
                     
                     <note>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Incomplete at the end. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>A Talmudic lexicon.</p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Each section deals with a letter of the alphabet, and is divided into chapters. The first section is preceded by a list giving the number of chapters in each of the twenty-two sections, and noting combinations of of letters not extant in the lexicon. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Volume 1 ends with the beginning of the article on כלבום, continuing without a break at the opening of volume 2. </p>
                     
                     
                     
                     </note>
                     
                     
                     
                     <filiation>Uniform with Or 1264 (volume 1 of the same work). Cf. the contents of Add MS 26881.</filiation>
                  
                  
                  
                  </msItem>
               
               
               
               </msContents>
               
               
               
               <physDesc rend="visible">
                  
                  
                  
                  <p>Parchment and paper codex of the 14th century.</p>
                  
                  
                  
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     
                     
                     
                     <supportDesc material="mixed">
                        
                        
                        
                        <support>Parchment and paper (folios 1-78: paper with outer and inner sheets of the quires are made of parchment; folios 79-153: parchment).</support>
                        
                        
                        
                        <extent>153 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              
                              
                              
                              <height>345</height>
                              
                              
                              
                              <width>280</width>
                           
                           
                           
                           </dimensions>
                           
                           
                           
                           <dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
                              
                              
                              
                              <height>295</height>
                              
                              
                              
                              <width>205</width>
                           
                           
                           
                           </dimensions>
                        
                        
                        
                        </extent>
                        
                        
                        
                        <foliation>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>153 folios (+ 1 unfoliated paper flyleaf at the beginning and at the end). </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        </foliation>
                        
                        
                        
                        <collation>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>11 quires: i-iii<hi rend="sup">20</hi>, iv<hi rend="sup">18</hi>, v-ix<hi rend="sup">10</hi>, x<hi rend="sup">14-1</hi> (half of the 6th bifolium is cut off, the other half [folio 137] is heavily mutilated), xi<hi rend="sup">14-2</hi>. Catchwords have been cut off when rebound, but still visible on the unmutilated leaves (lower margins have been folded, not cut). </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        </collation>
                        
                        
                        
                        <condition>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Tidemark at head, sometimes at edges. </p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Front paper leaves repaired/infilled before rebinding. </p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Incomplete at the end. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        </condition>
                     
                     
                     
                     </supportDesc>
                     
                     
                     
                     <layoutDesc>
                        
                        
                        
                        <layout columns="1" ruledLines="39" writtenLines="39">
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Uniform layout.</p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Hair and flesh sides are distinguishable. </p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Visible pricking and hard-point ruling.</p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Many leaves irregularly shaped, some folded (folios 133, 146, 150, 151 152), probably due to trimming by later re-binding. </p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Initial and final words in square characters, headings in square characters and partly in red ink. </p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Marginal and in-between columns notes. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        </layout>
                     
                     
                     
                     </layoutDesc>
                  
                  
                  
